1.  Install a package manager (Homebrew)

    ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"

2.  Change your terminal to the Tests directory

3.  Install composer
    curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | php

    Or if you don't have curl:
    php -r "readfile('https://getcomposer.org/installer');" | php
    
4.  Read the json file and import the required libraries  
    
    ./composer.phar update â€“dev
    
5.  Now to install php unit.
    First we'll need wget
    
    brew install wget

    wget https://phar.phpunit.de/phpunit.phar
    
    chmod +x phpunit.phar
    
    mv phpunit.phar /usr/local/bin/phpunit
6.  Copy settings.example into settings.json and enter your api credentials there
7.  Download example articles form https://appleseed.apple.com/sp/downloads/projects/1000851
    and move them to ./Example_Articles
8.  Run test
    
    phpunit